                            <comment id="120516" author="eugenparaschiv" created="Tue, 13 Oct 2015 15:52:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Getting support for the JSON-API spec into Spring would be fantastic. &lt;br/&gt;
A quick note and common question is how does it differ from HAL? Here&apos;s a very quick look into the differences: &lt;a href=&quot;http://jsonapi.org/faq/#why-not-use-the-hal-specification&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://jsonapi.org/faq/#why-not-use-the-hal-specification&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Finally - it would definitely be worth looking at Katharsis and - if possible - basing the implementation on that. &lt;br/&gt;
Cheers, &lt;br/&gt;
Eugen. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="120517" author="sdeleuze" created="Tue, 13 Oct 2015 16:22:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Indeed, having a look at client side library support for these technologies may also help to to see how JSON API use cases differ from HAL ones (both seems to have significant adoption):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://jsonapi.org/implementations/#client-libraries-javascript&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;JSON API Javascript libraries&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/mikekelly/hal_specification/wiki/Libraries#javascript&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;HAL Javascript libraries&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://projects.spring.io/spring-hateoas/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Spring HATEOAS&lt;/a&gt; already supports HAL as a default rendering. That said, I am not sure if JSON API is something that makes sense or not in Spring HATEOAS context, and not sure what is the nature of the relationship between Spring HATEOAS/Spring Data REST and Katharsis, but &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=olivergierke&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;olivergierke&quot;&gt;Oliver Gierke&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=gregturn&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;gregturn&quot;&gt;Greg Turnquist&lt;/a&gt; feedback may help here &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="120527" author="amaltson" created="Tue, 13 Oct 2015 18:56:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This would be amazing, getting a large framework like Spring behind JSON-API will help propel the much needed standard to large enterprises.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="120537" author="sdeleuze" created="Wed, 14 Oct 2015 07:31:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=eugenparaschiv&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;eugenparaschiv&quot;&gt;Eugen Paraschiv&lt;/a&gt; Katharsis annotated model approach is really interesting, but it seems there is also some overlap with what is currently supported in Spring HATOAS / Spring Data REST (resource, id, repositories). Leveraging these capabilities to support JSON API seems also an interesting option.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Do you have any specific concerns/wishes/ideas about an upcoming JSON API support in Spring HATOAS (as an alternative to HAL)?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="120625" author="masterspambot" created="Sat, 17 Oct 2015 13:56:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hello guys,&lt;br/&gt;
This is @masterspambot from Katharsis. I&apos;m very glad that you guys are also interested in providing compatibility to JSON:API! A few weeks ago we finished our roadmap to 1.0.0 version,  to move library from prototype stage. Currently we want to expand support for Spring framework (mainly Spring Data) on versions 2.0.0 and 3.0.0, but firstly we need to minimise the impact of overlapping functionalities with Spring and make library a little bit more elastic to finally make spring-katharsis adapter easily integrable. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So if you wish to help and share you knowledge, ideas and creativity just contact us. We&apos;d be more than happy for your support. Let&apos;s work on this solution together &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="120640" author="sdeleuze" created="Sun, 18 Oct 2015 11:32:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hey &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=masterspambot&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;masterspambot&quot;&gt;B&#322;a&#380;ej Krysiak&lt;/a&gt;, happy to hear that you have Spring support in your roadmap, I will be happy to help and discuss with you about that maybe on Katharsis Google group or in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/katharsis-project/katharsis-spring&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/katharsis-project/katharsis-spring&lt;/a&gt; issues when this module will be created.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As discussed with &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=gregturn&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;gregturn&quot;&gt;Greg Turnquist&lt;/a&gt;, such support also perfectly makes sense in Spring HATEOAS, so I have created a &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-hateoas/issues/402&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Spring HATEAOAS issue&lt;/a&gt; for JSON API support, and I will be happy to help also here, and perhaps contribute.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As consequence, I set this issue target version to &quot;Pending Closure&quot; since JSON API support seems to make sense in a Katharsis Spring module or in Spring HATEAOAS, not in Spring Framework itself.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="120834" author="sdeleuze" created="Thu, 22 Oct 2015 09:26:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I mark this issue as duplicate since JSON API support will be implemented on &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-hateoas/issues/402&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Spring HATEOAS&lt;/a&gt; side + by a Katharsis Spring module.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
